dict.string: [Functional] Fixes ThinkPads breathing light of the Power Button LED will not return to normal after waking up. Also fixes an issue where the F4 microphone indicator status is not normal after waking up on older ThinkPad models.
[Cosmetic] Attaches an AC Adapter Device existing in a Laptop's DSDT to the AppleACPIACAdapter service in the IORegistry of macOS.
[Cosmetic] Adds Direct Memory Access Controller (DMAC) device to IORegistry.
[Functional] Adds a fake Embedded Controller (SSDT-EC) and enables USB Power Management (SSDT-EC-USBX).
[Functional] Fixing Shutdows/Restart. Due to a missing S5 call that powers down the controller.
[Cosmetic] Adds Fake Firmware Hub Device (FWHD) device to the IORegistry in macOS.
[Functional] Fixes IRQ conflicts. Required for on-board sound to work.
[Functional] OS Check Fix patch to simulate a version of Windows for Darwin.
[Functional] Allow the kernel's XCPM(XNU's CPU Power Management) to manage CPU's power management.
[Functional] It specifically brings back NVRAM support and requires very little configuration for the end user.
[Functional] Adds Backlight Control for Laptop Screens.
[Functional] Fixes System Management Bus and Memory Controller in macOS.
RTL8111/8168/8411 PCI Express Gigabit Ethernet Controller
V1.6.7 | [Lilu] An open source kernel extension bringing a platform for arbitrary kext, library, and program patching throughout the system for macOS.
V1.3.2 | [CPUMon] a member of VirtualSMC that provides power info of processor
V1.6.6 | [Graphics] Various patches necessary for certain ATI/AMD/Intel/Nvidia GPUs. This is needed for Intel HD 620.
V1.8.9 | [Audio] Enable native macOS audio support
V1.1.1 | [SSD] Enable native power management for 3rd-party NVMe devices
V1.2.7 | [Processor] A Lilu plug-in for dynamic power management data injection.
V1.1.5 | [Services] Kernel extension for enabling Sidecar, NightShift, AirPlay to Mac and Universal Control support
V1.4.9 | [Hibernate] Kexts for fixing S4 hibernation & wakeup
V1.1.2 | [Lilu] Kernel extension for blocking unwanted processes causing compatibility issues on different hardware and unlocking the support for certain features restricted to other hardware.
V2.3.5 | [PS2] PS/2 keyboard / touchpad driver framework
V1.0.3 | [Keyboard] Fixes brightness keys on keyboard.
V2.4.2 | [Ethernet] Realtek RT8168 Ethernet driver (supports up to 100Mbps)
